caption: Staff is so nice, and the food is great too!

Great bagels! Great coffee! Great value! When office workers were huddled in their homes during the pandemic these workers showed up. One of my families favorite spots in the neighborhood and we’ve yet to have a disappointing meal. Thanks!

We had the Crunchy Spice bagel sandwich for breakfast and it was super delicious!!! It was nice and spicy and just had the best flavor profile! A little on the pricey side, but it was totally worth it. (We went to the Hayes location when we were in San Francisco.)
Best bagels in the city. Bring the turmeric latte back.

Ordered a club sandwich. Mustard was not listed on the menu as part of the sandwich, but was on the sandwich and sadly I hate mustard. So I didn’t enjoy it at all. Also ordered a veggie deluxe bagel. It was only ok- really salty.  We also …

Ordered the smoked salmon supposedly comes with capers came with none had to ask and I was eating I looked in the bag and no napkins like I wonder if they go eat without napkins as well just wondering because if the answer is no then why …
SF is lucky to have three of these timeless and classic places offered by the same family. A staple. L'Chaim!
Good food

The BEST place in Hayes Valley to experience a real DELI. Great staff and great food. Please support our local business'. Everything here is house-made. We need to keep this gem in our neighborhood. Everything I have ordered here was …
Awesome sandwiches, (possibly best in San Francisco). Still awesome after all these years.
I used to love this place. But this morning was the second time the bagel was completely untoasted, even after specifically emphasizing I wanted it well toasted.
Awesome bagels sandwiches. Enough said.
Expensive and mediocre

The customer service is excellent considering you need to order outside and only briefly. The bagels were delicious. I ordered an everything bagel, toasted with shmear (not cream cheese) and smashed avocado. I also tried a cup of their cold brew ice coffee and it gave me a nice morning jolt!
Good, but expensive for what it is.
Bagel cafe in Hayes Valley. Nice location and good service
Bagel is 4/5, but still looking for the rest of the avocado on it

Though the bagels and other food can be top notch - the attention to detail is lacking - and poorly managed - more than once I have ordered  a “Baker’s dozen” of bagels - that’s supposed to mean 13 rather than 12 - but here I have never …

Very disappointed  the young lady who took my order at the Octavia street  location was very rude both times I visit this place and the bagels are very hard I tried toasted and non toasted both ways were hard as a rock .I visited this place two times and I won't be back I will stick with  Noah Bagels.
Food was very good. Service by a female coworker was very short and un-helpful when asked questions. Other staff member took over and was helpful.
They know what they are doing!!!
Very friendly staff, excellent bagels (the Lox bagel was awesome!)
Some staffs are not friendly at all
Super solid bagels

Got two sesame seed bagel egg sandwiches and they were so. stinking. GOOD! Very quick service and the eco-friendly packaging was very much appreciated. Found this place via google and I'm VERY happy I did. Got my NY bagel fix on the other coast!
Great bagels, staff are always friendly
Great gluten free bagels! They aren't on the menu so you have to ask which is annoying.

Bagel itself was delicious but I was really disappointed with the crispy pastrami, was expecting a bunch of slices like you usually get at a deli, but instead got this one TINY slice of what looked like burned bacon. The egg also felt …

Massively disappointing. A whole lot of money for a whole lot of nothing. Breakfast sandwich? $9. $2 for a single slice of pastrami. If the bagels were toasted like I asked for, I couldn't tell. Bagels too dense. Maybe this city just has a low bar for bagels? Regardless, I won't be returning and would not recommend.
Great neighborhood bagel spot. Fresh bagels and really good chocolate babka! Pro tip: ask for your bagel double toasted. Also try their crispy pastrami!
(Translated by Google) Very good seasoning, highly recommended  (Original) Muy buen sazón, altamente recomendado
Delicious Reuben

Tasty bagels, but the staff will never get your order right. I come here once a week usually on weekends and every time they mess up my order (but I keep coming back, the bagels are good). Whatever you tell the cashier don’t expect it to …
Everything bagels are coated on both sides which is great! Got the egg and cheese w pastrami (9$) and egg w harissa (7$). Harissa wasn’t spicy at all and slathered all over (too much for my liking ).
Great place fabulous bagels
There was a line out the door the entire time I was there.  So delicious is dangerous.  This would be my daily breakfast go to spot if I lived in San Fran...
Amazing bagels, nothing more to add. One star deduction because the quality of the coffee varied on several visits here
Bagels are solid (for CA) but small and not worth the ludicrous prices.
Fresh bagels,  nice place to chill..no public WiFi :(

UPDATE: They still have awful service. Here’s a photo of the only TWO tellers assembling boxes while a huge line of people wait. Don’t bother.  Service is slow (their POS seems hard to use). Bagels are fine, but expensive. Sandwiches are good. Coffee is decent — but they are ALWAYS out of cold brew.
Bagels good.   Ok Coffee.
Amazing bagels really fast and friendly service!!
They use square POS machines and are a very close partner to Square.
The bagels are small, so don't you dare be ashamed to eat three in one go.
Amazing bagels and brekkie place!
Great tasty bagels in a lovely neighborhood with friendly staff

Good place to have a quick snack/lunch. Not too busy when we went there. Had a good view of the street to chill for a bit. Mrs had a Reuben which she enjoyed very much. I had a (Kinda) Spicy Egg with Onion Bialy Bagel which was fine when adding some mustard on it, personally.

I've had much better bagels in SF. Have given this a couple of chances but the bagels are quite dry and on the small size. I suspect the bagels were a day old. Babka has been hit and miss and on one occasion was definitely from the previous day.
Usually very good bagels but often hit or miss depending on the day.
Such a unexpected gem of a place! Go here! Options for everyone and really tasty bagles. So happy I found this place!
Legit bagel and latke. I've never heard of horseradish and dill cream cheese but it was delicious. These bagels are similar to ones I had at a Jewish bakery in Montreal. Yum.

I was excited to see this branch of Wise Sons pop up around the corner from my house - and they had black and white cookies on the menu! I’m a black and white addict so I grabbed some today. Guys these cookies are an absolute insult. Dry, …
Good clean environment, but maybe a little pricey for what you get.
Super tasty and wide menu. Just wanted to order everything. Recommend checking it out if in the area
The sandwiches are just ok, the matzoh ball soup is great, the balls themselves are tasty, but the broth is a little thin, could be heartier
Very overrated. The bagels are truly awful though not worse than all the bagels tend to be outside of the NY area. Egg sandwich is mediocre. The hot food is better.
Great bagels and sandwiches!

Reuben was great but a little pricey ($12.50!) considering the portion size. Their signature corned beef was a let down - meat was pretty dry, and again, not a particularly generous serving for the price. Pickles are a little on the bland side.

Both the salmon lox and pastrami lox were very good but the bagel was stale. Moldy challah visible to customers. Price too high for quality. Maybe passable if you've never had a fresh bagel before. Otherwise a disappointment

Great bagels! An excellent spot for authentic Jewish bakery classics.  The pickles are a bit bland, but all the other food is on point. The coffee rocks! One of the only places around that can make a dirty chai and not burn it.
Big fan of the Reuben
Maybe the worst bagel I've ever had, and I waited an hour to find out they were out of virtually every flavor by 11:30. Just close the doors if you run out of all of your food. Won't be back.
Great flavors, and even greater service.

The food here is good but overpriced. Also, I wish they had the full menu! The Wise Sons with the full menu is legit. This is just a pared down version (similar to the location on Fillmore) with sandwiches and bagels. The bagels are good but not huge. This is a pretty small location, there is limited seating.
The servers here are great but I find the bagles and mazo ball soup just aren't memorable
Rueben Sandwich was Great, friendly staff and nice area
Great place to have delivered because the inside of the place is very small. No place to sit and eat comfortably.

So great to have a great breakfast and lunch option in Hayes Valley. They serve Stumptown Coffee with cold brew on tap! They have recently added classic sandwiches to their menu and have salads when you're looking for a healthier option.

Bagel slightly too tough and hard, the contents ooze out the sides when you bite down. Only used one thin slice of smoked salmon and something in the contents (maybe capers/dill or the everything bagel itself?) made it taste hella salty. The cream cheese was high quality though.
Have seen the staff multiple times handling food directly with bare hands, no gloves on
Incredibly friendly and incredibly yummy! Couldn't wish for more!
The one great measure of an excellent East Coast bagel w/schmear, is the toast on the bagel. Nothing worse than a doughy bialy loaded with cream cheese.

Delicious classic "Jewish" style deli sandwiches,  very tasty and high quality meats and breads. I get the no. 19, corned beef and cole slaw. Also has one of the best lox bagels I've ever had. Restricted hours are unfortunate!

I was in Octavia Park at lunchtime, and I noticed a woman eating what looked like a delicious hot bagel sandwich. I asked her where she bought it and she pointed me to Wise Sons, a Jewish deli.  They don't have a lot of vegetarian options …
Amazing bagels. Wouldn't recommend their coffee, but there are plenty of better coffee options in the neighborhood.
Tasty coffee and dope breakfast sandwiches. Definitely recommend the crispy pastrami. Some outdoor seating available.
Got the stumptown cold brew. Pretty tasty and a decent amount of coffee for $4
Nice bagel and sandwich place. Gets very busy around breakfast / early brunch time.
Good kosher food.
Decent bagels and schmear. If you’re from New York, you’ll be disappointed.
The bees knees.  I like half smoked salmon schmear and horseradish schmear.  Go now and dont hesitate.   These bagels cant wait!
Best bagels
Perfect. So glad we now have Wise Sons in Hayes Valley. Lox and cream cheese on a warm freshly baked bagel loaded with sesame seeds. Oh yeah.
Delicious coffee, bagel smears, great staff.

The bagels are great and the cappuccino is, too. However quite expensive.
Best cup of standard drip I’ve had in SF and really tasty bagels too!

I gotta agree with the person who wrote that this Wise Son isn’t really run that well, let me explain myself, i came into this store with high expectations the guy behind the counter was super friendly because when i was going to sign the …
Perfect addition to Hayes Valley, a little neighbourhood bakery! Really friendly people, tasty bagels and on a side street overlooking trees.
Not as well run as the Fillmore shop just yet.
Try the salt bagel!
I love bagels, and this place has some exceptional pastrami-spiced lox. It opened 5 days ago, and I have been 4 times since it opened. I expect I will be back many times.
Bright and clean little spot to grab coffee, a quick bite or traditional deli to-go -- best bagels and bialys on the west coast!!
